import React from "react";
import { Container, Nav, Navbar, NavDropdown } from "react-bootstrap";
import { Link } from "react-router-dom";
import { GoBriefcase, GoDeviceMobile } from "react-icons/go";
import { FaRoute } from "react-icons/fa";

export default function NavigationBar() {
  return (
    <header>
      <Container fluid className="topbar">
        <Link to="/"><GoBriefcase/> CAREERS</Link>
        <Link to="/contact"><GoDeviceMobile/> CONTACT US</Link>
        <Link to="/"><FaRoute/> CHECK MY ORDER</Link>
        <Link to="/">(000) 000-0000</Link>
      </Container>
      <Navbar collapseOnSelect expand="lg">
        <Navbar.Brand href="/">Ship Easy Now</Navbar.Brand>
        <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="responsive-navbar-nav" />
        <Navbar.Collapse id="responsive-navbar-nav">
          <Nav className="mr-auto">
          <Nav.Link href="/">HOW IT WORKS?</Nav.Link>
            <NavDropdown title="WHY SHIP EASY NOW?" id="collasible-nav-dropdown">
              <NavDropdown.Item href="/">Action</NavDropdown.Item>
              <NavDropdown.Item href="/">Another action</NavDropdown.Item>
              <NavDropdown.Item href="/">Something</NavDropdown.Item>
              <NavDropdown.Divider />
              <NavDropdown.Item href="#">Separated link</NavDropdown.Item>
            </NavDropdown>
            <Nav.Link href="/downloadapp">APP</Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href="/help">HELP</Nav.Link>
          </Nav>
          <Nav>
            <Link to="/signin" className="btn button">
              Sign In
            </Link>
            <Link to="/register" className="btn button-second link">
              Register
            </Link>
          </Nav>
        </Navbar.Collapse>
      </Navbar>
    </header>
  );
}
